cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with facial expression recognition using 3D geometric and 2D photometric attributes. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of visualizations and experiments on a database suggest that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
